import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country').size().reset_index(name='count')
    data = data.sort_values('count', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['latitude']]
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('latitude').count().reset_index()
    plt.scatter(data['latitude'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport locations by latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['longitude']]
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('longitude').sum().reset_index()
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['count'])
    plt.axvline(data['longitude'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['longitude'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport locations by longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airport_names = data['name'].tolist()
    airport_names_str = ' '.join(airport_names)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                min_font_size = 10).generate(airport_names_str)
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None) 
    plt.imshow(wordcloud) 
    plt.axis("off") 
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
